He was said to have prayed aloud in the Capitol on the Kalends of January that he might owe 4oo,ooo sesterces, explaining his prayer to one who asked him the meaning of it, by saying that he owed at the time 800,ooo. Some have supposed, but without good grounds, that he was the Pantolabus of Sat. 1. 8, 11.
